Determined to ensure transparency, accountability and value for money, the Nigeria Union of Journalists (NUJ), Yobe State Council on Sunday tracked the project approved by Governor Mai Mala Buni for the execution of 17 community development projects in Yusufari Local Government Area of the state. Alhaji Waziri Ibrahim, Chairman, Yusufari LGA told the inspection crew that the projects were executed in different parts of the area, which according to him include drilling of 21 boreholes at the cost of N 207.7 million, conversion of 9 generator boreholes to the solar system. Others projects are the reconstruction of Yusufari Emir’s palace at the cost of N 99 million, supply, installation and furnishing of Chairman’s official residence along with staff quarters and offices at N201, 018, 904.10. Federal Lawmaker, Zakariya Empowers 1,161 Constituents In Yobe Tikau Emirate Turbans 6 District Heads In Yobe The Council Chairman noted that Governor Buni also constructed and renovated Kumagannam General Hospital at the cost of N394..8 million, upgraded comprehensive health to the general hospital in Yusufari at the sum of N271.6 million among others. He commanded Buni and the Ministry for Local Government for siting various development projects within the local government. On his part, Rajab Muhammed, the team lead of the Journalists, said the inspection exercise was aimed at promoting accountability and good governance in the state.